{
  "texts": [
    "Sample-selection methods typically perform sample reweighting to down-weight unreliable instances [26]- [29].",
    "This category also includes data pruning [30], which filters out potentially noisy samples, though its pruning ratio often requires scenario-specific tuning and can be inefficient in practice.",
    "Representative selection approaches include MentorNet [10], which learns a curriculum to guide the student model.",
    "Labelcorrection methods instead aim to revise noisy annotations directly [31], [32], such as Meta Label Correction [33], noisechannel models [34]- [36] or influence-based methods [37].2) Co-teacher Framework: Co-teaching-based methods mitigate the confirmation bias caused by noisy labels by training multiple peer networks that exchange potential knowledge during learning [38].",
    "This mutual-teaching mechanism helps each model avoid overfitting to the specific noise patterns memorized by the other."
  ]
}